      "writtenOn": "2020-12-11T21:00:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Major: I think this works well for Project Manager, but maybe a bit tricky for RunManager, because the state of ProjectManager is exclusively determined by a single entity while for RunManager it is determined by Run entity and its children. \n\nRunManger may workaround by coming up with a EVersion the represents a snapshot of Run entity and its children. An alternative way I can think of is to drop the concept of EVersion completely in the event box and call GetState again at the beginning at the transaction. We can check state staleness by make State\n\n```\ntype State interface {\n  Same(other State) bool\n}\n```\n\nEVersion could also be part of the state so that SaveState could compute the newEVersion inside the implementation itself",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 142,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "c2dec9117b9db36b40679239526f7f6756a9923f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8952ea47_6e2789c2",
        "filename": "cv/internal/eventbox/box.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 147,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-12T00:20:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Project M (PM) isn\u0027t necessarily different from Run M (RM), we may have extra entities, just not ye.\nMy thinking is that EVersion would be *only* in the main entity,\nand iff other entities have to be updated, then we\u0027d also always update the main entity, even if it means just doing EV++ (minor con: requires needlessly cloning a state to get a new pointer)\n\nWhat you propose is also OK, however, it\u0027d require you to read *all* child entities to construct a state.\nThis shouldn\u0027t be necessary even for RunManager.\nSuppose, RunManager gets a CLUpdated event. Processing such event should start with reading just Run itself (if it is stopped, then no need to do anything) and then specific RunCL entity to determine if anything needs to be done at all.",
      "parentUuid": "0efe5402_791a3e6d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 142,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "c2dec9117b9db36b40679239526f7f6756a9923f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "230aecc4_8812e428",
        "filename": "cv/internal/eventbox/box.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 147,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-12T00:43:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the main entity is updated (i.e. eVersion increments) when its child entity is updated, then it is okay. I initially thought sometimes we don\u0027t need to even load the main entity back when updating the child entity. For example, when receiving a TryjobUpdateEvent that a tryjob has started, technically, updating the RunTryjob entity is sufficient enough. But for most of the cases, we\u0027ll need and load back the run entity.",
      "parentUuid": "8952ea47_6e2789c2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 142,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "c2dec9117b9db36b40679239526f7f6756a9923f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
